A political aspirant in Niger state identified as Abbas Bello has reportedly retrieved money from delegate after he lost his bid to pick his party’s primaries in the just concluded elections in the state.

Abbas Bello is said to be disappointed after investing money on delegates in order to get their votes. However, the politician got disappointed by the election results as his opponent was declared winner.
After the result was announced, the Bello asked all the delegates that collected his money to return to him immediately. In a viral video, the campaign manager of the politician was spotted collecting money from the delegates. The delegates were said have been paid 100,000 each.
Some of the delegates that return their money felt disappointed by the action of the politician.The viral video which was shared by American based Nigerian journalist, Adeola Fayehun has been attracting diverse reactions from Nigerians.
